16/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police Director Milorad Veljovic announced on Tuesday (December 15th) that the person sending death threats by mail from Chicago to Serbian officials has been identified. 
Serbian police and security services, working with US police and the FBI, have identified the person, whom Veljovic only described as having Serbian citizenship. 
Letters went to President Boris Tadic, Supreme Court President Nata Mesarovic, war crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic and other officials. 
Prosecutors in both Serbia and the US are deciding what to do next. 
(RTS, Tanjug, B92 - 15/12/09)
